abstract: On a snowy morning just days before Iowans make their choice in the Democratic presidential contest, Joe Biden invoked President Ronald Reagan, warning a small crowd that the nation was at risk of losing its identity as “that shining city on the hill."
snippet: On a snowy morning just days before Iowans make their choice in the Democratic presidential contest, Joe Biden invoked President Ronald Reagan, warning a small crowd that the nation was at risk of losing its identity as “that shining city on the h...
lead_paragraph: MASON CITY, Iowa — On a snowy morning just days before Iowans make their choice in the Democratic presidential contest, Joe Biden invoked President Ronald Reagan, warning a small crowd that the nation was at risk of losing its identity as “that shining city on the hill."
headline_main: Biden's 'Consensus' Pitch Faces Biggest Test in Iowa
headline_print_headline: Biden's 'Consensus' Pitch Faces Biggest Test in Iowa

abstract: Bernie Sanders was at 26 percent, Joe Biden at 25, Pete Buttigieg at 22 and Elizabeth Warren at 15 in a CBS News poll.
snippet: Bernie Sanders was at 26 percent, Joe Biden at 25, Pete Buttigieg at 22 and Elizabeth Warren at 15 in a CBS News poll.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — A new CBS News poll released Sunday shows Senator Bernie Sanders of Vermont and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. neck-and-neck in Iowa eight days before the caucuses.

abstract: President Donald Trump's impeachment trial enters a pivotal week as his defense team resumes its case and senators face a critical vote on whether to hear witnesses or proceed directly to a vote that is widely expected to end in his acquittal. The articles of impeachment charge Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.
snippet: President Donald Trump's impeachment trial enters a pivotal week as his defense team resumes its case and senators face a critical vote on whether to hear witnesses or proceed directly to a vote that is widely expected to end in his acquittal. The...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's impeachment trial enters a pivotal week as his defense team resumes its case and senators face a critical vote on whether to hear witnesses or proceed directly to a vote that is widely expected to end in his acquittal. The articles of impeachment charge Trump with abuse of power and obstruction of Congress.
headline_main: Defense Resumes in Key Impeachment Week; Dems Seek Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Defense Resumes in Key Impeachment Week; Dems Seek Witnesses

abstract: With four strong polls on Saturday and Sunday, Mr. Yang, who missed the last debate, has secured a spot onstage in New Hampshire on Feb. 7.
snippet: With four strong polls on Saturday and Sunday, Mr. Yang, who missed the last debate, has secured a spot onstage in New Hampshire on Feb. 7.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — The entrepreneur Andrew Yang qualified for the next Democratic debate with a string of four strong polls released in quick succession on Saturday and Sunday.

headline_main: Andrew Yang qualifies for the next debate.

abstract: A coveted Iowa surrogate says he called Pete Buttigieg the “next president” because that’s just something you say when someone visits the state. “It’s a courtesy,” he said.
snippet: A coveted Iowa surrogate says he called Pete Buttigieg the “next president” because that’s just something you say when someone visits the state. “It’s a courtesy,” he said.
lead_paragraph: STORM LAKE, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg had one of northwest Iowa’s most coveted surrogates introduce him before a town-hall-style event Saturday night at Buena Vista University: David Johnson, a former state senator who in 2016 quit the Republican Party when Donald J. Trump won its presidential nomination.
headline_main: A Klobuchar endorser switches to Buttigieg? Not quite.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren received the coveted endorsement from Iowa’s largest paper.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren received the coveted endorsement from Iowa’s largest paper.
lead_paragraph: MUSCATINE, Iowa — The Des Moines Register endorsed Senator Elizabeth Warren for the Democratic presidential nomination on Saturday night, calling her “the best leader for these times.”
headline_main: How Warren found out she won the Des Moines Register endorsement.

abstract: And we’re bringing you updates from the trail.
snippet: And we’re bringing you updates from the trail.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — We’re approaching the final week before the Iowa presidential caucuses, and the Democratic campaign pulsed with a newly urgent and frenetic energy on Sunday morning as the five top candidates descended on the state and a crush of new polls and endorsements came out.
headline_main: The Iowa caucuses are in 8 days.

abstract: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden appear locked in a tight race for the Democratic presidential nomination, as both campaigned in Iowa on Sunday with only days left until the first contest.
snippet: U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden appear locked in a tight race for the Democratic presidential nomination, as both campaigned in Iowa on Sunday with only days left until the first contest.
lead_paragraph: FORT DODGE, Iowa — U.S. Senator Bernie Sanders and former Vice President Joe Biden appear locked in a tight race for the Democratic presidential nomination, as both campaigned in Iowa on Sunday with only days left until the first contest.
headline_main: U.S. Presidential Hopefuls Sanders, Biden in Tight Race in Early Primary States
headline_print_headline: U.S. Presidential Hopefuls Sanders, Biden in Tight Race in Early Primary States

abstract: We sat down with Democratic presidential candidates and asked them a new set of questions, including how they’d debate President Trump to the last book they read.
snippet: We sat down with Democratic presidential candidates and asked them a new set of questions, including how they’d debate President Trump to the last book they read.
lead_paragraph: The first time we interviewed the Democratic presidential candidates, late last spring, we had a pile of yes-or-no, either-or policy questions to ask, many of them representing litmus-test issues at the heart of Democratic politics: single-payer health care and foreign wars, wealth concentration and tech regulation.
